HEADWORD: man-eating shark
<hw>man-eating shark</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A term applied to sharks
that attack humans, especially the great white shark (<spn>Carcharodon
carcharias</spn>), a large aggressive shark widespread in warm
seas.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> great white shark, white shark, man-eater,
<spn>Carcharodon carcharias</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maned</ent>⟦br⟧
